bq.You should use Option.setRequired() instead of hardcoding app-id.

You are saying the line ?
{code}
    formatter.printHelp("yarn logs -applicationId <application ID> [OPTIONS]", new Options());
{code}

This is just for printing message. (Try to print the help message as similar as proposed help message).
But for the option which will be actually used in command, the input parameter does be required.
{code}
    opts.addOption(APPLICATION_ID_OPTION, true, "ApplicationId (required)");
{code}

Added test case to test help message in the new patch

